        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. The global production volume is extrapolated from the European production volume based on reports from Cefic (European Chemical Industry Council), and the American Chemistry Council.  
According to Cefic (2016) the Global sales of chemicals in the year 2015 was 3 534 billion euros. The reported share of sales per regions are: EU28 14.7%; Other Europe (Switzerland, Norway, Turkey, Russia and Ukraine) 2.7%; NAFTA (US, Canada and Mexico) 16.5%; Latin America 3.8%; China 39.9%; Japan 3.9%; Republic of Korea 3.2%; India 2.2%; Rest of Asia 11.9%; Rest of the World 1.3%. Cefic also reports the US total sales, 518.7 billion euros of the global 3 534 billion euros (14.7%). The same share is reported from the American Chemistry Council (2016), according to this source the USA sales account for 15% of global sales for the year 2016. 
According to the OECD the European market of copper for 2012 was 5.2 million tonnes. Coated copper flakes represent less than 0.1% and is further assumed that copper oxide accounts for 1/4 of the coated copper flakes. Using those assumptions, the amount of copper oxide produced is 1300 tonnes per year. Since no data were found for the global production this value was scaled accordingly.

Reference(s):
Cefic 2016. Facts and figures 2016 of the European chemical industry. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Facts-and-Figures/Chemicals-Industry-Profile/ 
American Chemistry Council 2016. Outlook: U.S. Chemical Industry Continues to Outpace Industrial Output; Accounts for More Than One-Half of Construction Spending by Manufacturing Sector. Accessible at: https://www.americanchemistry.com/Media/PressReleasesTranscripts/ACC-news-releases/US-Chemical-Industry-Continues-to-Outpace-Industrial-Output.html. OECD. 2014. Screening Information Dataset, Initial Assessment Profile for Copper and copper compounds. Retrieved from: http://webnet.oecd.org/hpv/ui/handler.axd?id=2352a0b6-1872-4c4f-adb9-f2782d183f92, 4 July 2017.</productionVolumeComment>
